HOW TO SETUP THE ENVIRONMENT:
------------------------------------
1. Download and install 2.7.x - https://www.python.org/downloads/
2. Download and install Aptana Studio 3 - http://www.aptana.com/products/studio3/download.html
3. Download and install Google App Engine SDK for Python - https://cloud.google.com/appengine/downloads#Google_App_Engine_SDK_for_Python
4. Download and install GitHub for Windows - https://windows.github.com/
5. In GitHub for Windows: Clone "siage" from github.
6. Rename the cloned "siage" folder to "siage2"
7. In Aptana Studio 3: Create a new Google App Engine project called "siage".
7.1 Under new -> other -> PyDev -> PyDev Google App Engine project
7.2 Follow the guide and create an empty project for "si-age-league". This is probably not important.
8. Copy content of "siage2" into "siage".
9. In GitHub for Windows: Locate the siage folder again if necessary.

HOW TO MAKE YOUR FIRST LOCAL CHANGE:
------------------------------------
1. Start Google App Engine Launcher (SDK)
2. File -> Add Existing Application -> Select the "siage" folder.
3. Start it and browse it.
4. Make changes in Aptana Studio 3 and see the changes live.

HOW TO DEPLOY CHANGES 
------------------------------------
1. Commit to github
2a. Wait 10min for the build engine to detect the change
2b. Or manually deploy it: http://104.154.82.208/jenkins/
2c. Deploy it with Google App Engine SDK